data.chText: 她紧紧地把他抱在胸前。
data.enText: She pressed him to her bosom.
the part of a piece of clothing that covers a woman's bosom

data.chText: 别在她胸襟上的一朵玫瑰
data.enText: a rose pinned to her bosom

data.chText: 和爱护自己的人在一起的情形；在…的怀抱中
data.enText: a situation in which you are with people who love and protect you

data.chText: 生活在家庭的温暖怀抱中
data.enText: to live in the bosom of your family

word_means: 和爱护自己的人在一起的情形

means: 和爱护自己的人在一起的情形

tr: a close affectionate and protective acceptance
example: his willing embrace of new ideas
in the bosom of the family

tr: cloth that covers the chest or breasts
either of two soft fleshy milk-secreting glandular organs on the chest of a woman
the locus of feelings and intuitions
example: in your heart you know it is true
her story would melt your bosom

tr: the chest considered as the place where secret thoughts are kept
example: his bosom was bursting with the secret

tr: squeeze (someone) tightly in your arms, usually with fondness
example: He hugged her close to him

value.def: A woman's breasts are sometimes referred to as her bosom or her bosoms.

example.ex: ...a large young mother with a baby resting against her ample bosom.
example.tran: 让怀中婴儿靠在她丰满胸部上的身材高大的年轻母亲

value.def: If you are in the bosom of your family or of a community, you are among people who love, accept, and protect you.

example.ex: Joan was delighted to welcome her boyfriend into the bosom of her large, close-knit family.
example.tran: 琼十分高兴地欢迎她的男朋友加入她亲密无间的大家庭。

value.def: A bosom friend is a friend who you know very well and like very much indeed.

example.ex: Sakota was her cousin and bosom pal.
example.tran: 沙科塔是她的表妹和亲密伙伴。

value.def: If you take someone or something to your bosom, you accept them and treat or regard them with great affection.

example.ex: We, at least, have taken her to our bosom.
example.tran: 至少我们对她是关爱有加的。
